                       <p style="color: #00889B; font-size: 10px;">(Vitelliform macular dystrophy)</p>
                       <hr style="background-color:#BBBBBB; height:5px;">
                   </center>
                   <p style="color: #66B9BF;">
                       Best Disease affects a tiny part of the retina in the back of your eye, which is called the macula. It causes problems in central vision, but does not lead to total loss of vision or pain. The disorder starts causing changes in ages 3-15, but does not affect vision until later in life. This disease normally affects both eyes, but sometimes it affects only one.
                   </p>
